1. PRIVACY AND DATA PROTECTION REQUIREMENTS

1.1 Immediate Data Deletion
All facial images, biometric data, embeddings, and derived representations 
MUST be deleted immediately after age verification processing is complete. 
"Immediately" means within 1 second of completion or upon error termination.

1.2 No Long-Term Storage
The Software MUST NOT store, archive, cache, or retain any facial images, 
biometric templates, or personally identifiable biometric data beyond the 
immediate processing session.

1.3 No Data Resale
Facial images, biometric data, age predictions, or any derived biometric 
information MUST NOT be sold, licensed, or monetized as data products.

1.4 Explicit Consent
Users MUST provide explicit, informed consent before any biometric processing 
occurs. Consent mechanisms must be clear, unambiguous, and auditable.

1.5 Transparency
All biometric processing workflows MUST be documented, auditable, and 
transparent to end users.

2. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS

2.1 All derivative works, implementations, or integrations MUST credit:
    - Project name: BetterAgeVerify
    - Original creator: luvaary

2.2 Attribution must appear in:
    - User-facing interfaces where age verification occurs
    - Technical documentation
    - Source code headers
    - Public-facing project descriptions

3. ENFORCEMENT AND LIABILITY

3.1 Violation of the Privacy and Data Protection Requirements (Section 1) 
constitutes a material breach of this license and immediately terminates 
all rights granted herein.

